                ECHO PLAYER As you attempt to step onto the bridge, you feel something like a scaly claw, larger than your body, holding you gently back. A voice whispers, so low that it could be in your mind, "You must be cleansed before you may enter the Hall." As you consider these words, you notice a flash of light, and looking, see a narrow crack in the mountainside to your right.
        ENDIF
ENDIF

ITEM 1 62 ADJ1=210 VAL2=2375

NUMBER 2375
NAME Split in the Mountainside
ASTRAL
CHANNEL 556

*DESCRIPTION_START
Surprisingly wide and open, the space behind the crack is filled with
sound, the thundering of falling water. This cataract is at the bottom of
a thin but powerful waterfall, plunging from some point high above where
it is open to the sky. You note with a practiced eye that the walls are
smoothed, magically no doubt, and the cataract is just large enough to
allow even an ungraceful dragon to descend or ascend. The water forms a
pool here, clean and cold, before passing through the narrow bottom and,
you suspect, emptying out as a second waterfall at a point below the
silvery mist beneath the ledge.
*DESCRIPTION_END

EXIT O 2374

