NUMBER 2377
NAME Temple of the Silent Ones
DEEPCAVE
CHANNEL 556

*DESCRIPTION_START
The inside of the temple seems larger than the outside, clearly visible
through the enormous opening in the mountainside, but it is not, really.
It is just so large and so well-illuminated that it seems to go on forever,
like a sky of polished stone. The walls themselves are formed into objects
and statues, shapes of ethereal beauty, magically pulled from the heartrock
of the mountains and merged with the outer stones. Veins of silver and
copper run through the walls, peeking from the surface in thin lines
that glitter in mysterious patterns older than the civilization which
gave you birth.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 0 72 ADJ1=163 VAL2=2376

EXIT NE 2378

;
;

NUMBER 2378
NAME Temple of the Silent Ones
CHANNEL 556
DEEPCAVE

*DESCRIPTION_START
Behold the progress of the beings you call dragons from beasts to beings
of power and grace! The walls of this chamber have been guided and shaped,
magically and with incredible skill, to show the slow evolution of the
dragons from their lowly origins to their current, perfect form. At one
end of the sculpted cavern, you see tiny lizards which run at the feet
of much larger ones, able to survive only because they are faster and
smarter than their lumbering neighbors. When the larger, clumsier creatures
die out as their eggs are eaten by a prototypical mammalian species, the
dragon ancestors fill the gap they have left behind, smart and fast enough
to defend their nests against the gnawing assaults. Their penultimate form
is the one this temple is built to honor, winged reptiles nearly as large
as the present species, with far less intelligence and no inherent magic.
These are the Silent Ones, dragons in all but name, who had not yet heard
the Song of the Universe which would make them what they are to this day.
*DESCRIPTION_END

EXIT SW 2377
EXIT NW 2379

;
;

NUMBER 2379
NAME Temple of the Silent Ones
DEEPCAVE
CHANNEL 556

*DESCRIPTION_START
All that glitters is here, brought from the lower reaches of the planet's
crust by the gentle guidance of draconic voices, scaled fingers and ancient
magic. Lines of gold, refined from the ore through fireless spells, rise
slightly from the glass-smooth walls, interwoven with silver and copper, a
few rare strands of platinum shot through the whole. They form the setting
for gems, rubies and emeralds, not cut but molded, as a Highlander would,
brought to perfection without the marring touch of a cutter's tools. This
is the honorary Hoard of the Silent Ones, who did not know the pleasures
of gold and silver in life, and are now afforded the greatest treasures of
their species as payment for birthing the race who honors them.
*DESCRIPTION_END

EXIT SE 2378
EXIT NE 2381

;
;

NUMBER 2380
NAME Temple... ash piles
DEEPCAVE
CHANNEL 556

*DESCRIPTION_START
This chamber is large enough to hold an entire human village, or that of
the Korvatae which sits beyond the mountainside. As such it is the smallest
of the sculpted caverns you have seen so far. Its center is discolored with
ashes, and heap after heap of ashes rests on the floor, against the walls,
some gathered into huge piles like small mountains within the mountain,
others only slightly taller than you are.
*DESCRIPTION_END

EXIT O 2381

;
;

NUMBER 2381
NAME Temple... the Wheel
DEEPCAVE
CHANNEL 556

*DESCRIPTION_START
The largest room in the ancient temple is also the simplest. No gold or
silver, no precious gems or fantastic sclupture is present here, merely
the simplest of lines, arranged with a classical beauty that somehow takes
your breath away. They all meet at a point in the northmost wall, and you
recall words you have heard spoken, that the dragons who die go to the
north, always, always to the north. At that point a wheel hangs down,
a wheel of silken threads woven into a familiar, yet strange, shape of
differently colored teardrops merged into a perfect circle. There are
not two colors, but five, and yet they come together, each perfectly
identical, each a fifth of the curling circle.
*DESCRIPTION_END

EXIT E 2380
EXIT SW 2379

